  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators aim to assess the respiratory effect of short half-life agents in balanced
      anesthesia on patients suffering from non-treated or suspected obstructive sleep apnea
      syndrome (OSA) We will study the impact on OSA of a regimen of remifentanil-desflurane versus
      a regimen of fentanyl-sevoflurane. Each patient will undergo three respiratory portable
      polygraphies: the night before the surgery ; the first night following the surgery ; the
      third night following the surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
